{"CreatedAt":"2026-05-12T14:16:29.000Z","Text":"We have just wrapped up the meta-issue which tracked type inference of all Elixir constructs: https://github.com/elixir-lang/elixir/issues/14558\n\nIt includes typing of the construct themselves and features like occurrence typing, to provide a high-degree of precision. Expect a new RC soon as we will continue measuring performance on our way to Elixir v1.20.","StatusId":"2054204067485024648","UserName":"Gada / ymtszw","UserProfileImageUrl":"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1520432647868391430/4b2AUYjC_normal.jpg","Retweet":"TRUE","EntitiesUrlsUrls":"","EntitiesUrlsExpandedUrls":"","ExtendedEntitiesMediaUrls":"","ExtendedEntitiesMediaTypes":"","ExtendedEntitiesMediaSourceUrls":"","ExtendedEntitiesMediaExpandedUrls":"","RetweetedStatusId":"2054204067485024648","RetweetedStatusFullText":"We have just wrapped up the meta-issue which tracked type inference of all Elixir constructs: https://github.com/elixir-lang/elixir/issues/14558\n\nIt includes typing of the construct themselves and features like occurrence typing, to provide a high-degree of precision. Expect a new RC soon as we will continue measuring performance on our way to Elixir v1.20.","RetweetedStatusUserName":"José Valim","RetweetedStatusUserProfileImageUrl":"https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/667973757181431808/IdQgSAH__200x200.jpg","RetweetedStatusEntitiesUrlsUrls":"https://github.com/elixir-lang/elixir/issues/14558","RetweetedStatusEntitiesUrlsExpandedUrls":"https://github.com/elixir-lang/elixir/issues/14558","RetweetedStatusExtendedEntitiesMediaUrls":"","RetweetedStatusExtendedEntitiesMediaTypes":"","RetweetedStatusExtendedEntitiesMediaSourceUrls":"","RetweetedStatusExtendedEntitiesMediaExpandedUrls":""}
